<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,799,1005]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1864" box="[151,307,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Halyomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,307,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Halyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an Old World genus, currently containing 37 species, primarily in the African, Oriental, and Southeast Asian regions. Several of the included species are probably synonyms of other species, and several others will probably be transferred to other related genera. There are no modern keys to all of the species; 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R. E." box="[1229,1436,907,933]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref54575" refString="Linnavuori, R. E. (1982) Pentatomidae and Acanthosomatidae (Heteroptera) of Nigeria and the Ivory Coast, with remarks on species of the adjacent countries in West and Central Africa. Acta Zoologica Fennica, 163, 1 - 176." type="journal article" year="1982">Linnavuori (1982)</bibRefCitation>
provided a key to some of the African species, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad, I. &amp; Zaidi, R. H." box="[727,988,943,969]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="237 - 253" refId="ref43390" refString="Ahmad, I. &amp; Zaidi, R. H. (1989) A revision of the genus Halyomorpha Mayr (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae: Pentatominae: Carpocorini) from Indo-Pakistan subcontinent with description of a new species from Potohar region of Pakistan and their cladistic analysis. Proceedings of the Pakistan Congress of Zoology, 9, 237 - 253." type="journal article" year="1989">Ahmad &amp; Zaidi (1989)</bibRefCitation>
provided a key to some of the Indo-Pakistan species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
